<b>Background</b>

<p>Developments towards <a href="/alpha_schema">NeuroML version 2.0</a> have been ongoing since the NeuroML workshop at <a href="http://math.la.asu.edu/~cans/workshop.html">Arizona State University
    in March 2010</a>. This meeting was an opportunity to discuss
    these developments, decide what is else is required, and lay plans for a formal v2.0 specification document.
    Topics for discussion at the workshop included:</p>

<ul>
<li>Representations of morphologies in NeuroML v2.0</li>

<li>Use of LEMS for defining spiking nodes, channels & synapses</li>

<li>Compatibility with SBML/CellML</li>

<li>Hierarchical network descriptions</li>

<li>Annotations and metadata </li>

<li>Movement to formalised standardisation process</li>

</ul>

<p>The agenda circulated prior to the meeting is available here: <a href="files/NeuroMLWorkshop2011.pdf">Agenda for 31st March & 1st April</a></p>

